<TITLE> Coco out on parole: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  Khaleda Zia's son Arafat Rahman Coco was freed from the custody of jail authorities on parole to attend the funeral of his grandmother Toyeba Majumdar Saturday, a prisons official said. Khaleda, former prime minister detained in special jail, will also be freed on parole for several hours to attend the funeral of Toyeba, the home ministry said in a statement. According to an official order, Khaleda was scheduled to stay on parole from 11am to 5pm. But Khaleda's lawyer advocate Mahbubuddin Khokon complained that the government was delaying the release of Khaleda. Tarique Rahman, elder of Khaleda's sons, will also be released on parole. A helicopter will carry the body of Toyeba to Dhaka from Dinajpur. DMP commissioner Naim Ahmed told bdnews24.com that the police put in place an adequate security arrangement for Khaleda and her two sons. Toyeba's son Shamim Eskanderaccompanied by his wifearrived in Dinajpur Saturday morning to take the body to Dhaka. Khaleda's lawyer Barrister Ahmed Azam Khan had earlier told bdnews24.com that the body of Toyeba would be flown to Dhaka Cantonment. The body will then be taken to Azad Mosque in Gulshan for a namaz-e-janaza after Asr prayers. The body will be flown back to Dinajpur town for burial. Toyeba died of heart attack at a Dinajpur hospital Friday, aged 87. bdnew
